======================================================================
Claim 2: -U_i is NOT a Veronese image (Schur T = -I excluded)
======================================================================

For W = -U to be a Veronese image, W + I/3 must be rank-1 PSD.
Check eigenvalues of -U_i + I/3:
  i = 0:  spec(W + I/3) = [0.666667, 0.666667, -0.333333]
           rank-1 PSD?  False  (rank-1 needs two zero eigenvalues + one positive)
  i = 1:  spec(W + I/3) = [0.666667, 0.666667, -0.333333]
           rank-1 PSD?  False  (rank-1 needs two zero eigenvalues + one positive)
  i = 2:  spec(W + I/3) = [0.666667, 0.666667, -0.333333]
           rank-1 PSD?  False  (rank-1 needs two zero eigenvalues + one positive)

Analytically: U_i has eigenvalues (2/3, -1/3, -1/3), so
  -U_i has eigenvalues (-2/3, 1/3, 1/3), and
  -U_i + I/3 has eigenvalues (-1/3, 2/3, 2/3).
This matrix has a NEGATIVE eigenvalue (-1/3), so it is NOT PSD.
Hence  -U_i + I/3  cannot equal  v v^T  for any v in R^3.
CONCLUSION: -U_i is NOT in the Veronese image of R^3.

